This paper is about the sample complexity of learning Sum-Product Networks (SPNs), which are a type of deep graphical model used for representing complex distributions. This topic falls under the broad area of machine learning, specifically in the sub-fields of probabilistic graphical models and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
